==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[אחאב|אַחְאָב]] (Ach'av = "father’s brother"); from אַח (ach = 'brother') + אָב (av = 'father').

===Proper noun===
'''Achab'''

# A king of [[Israel]] according to the [[Bible]].
# A male [[given name]].

